evision-v1','','','2018-09-10 02:00:02','2018-09-09 23:00:02','',115,'http://mynomadtales.maunty.ru/115-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(135,1,'2018-09-10 02:00:15','2018-09-09 23:00:15','Sydney-the capital of the Australian state Of new South Wales, colorful and diverse, the largest and oldest city in Australia located in the South-East of the country. Sydney was founded on 26 January 1788 by Arthur Philip, head of the first party of British colonists, and named after the English Minister of the interior Lord Sydney. It was granted city status on July 20, 1842.\r\n\r\nSydney offers a huge number of excursions and entertainment for every taste, there is everything - and the noisy fun of the big city and unity with wildlife, and a great beach holiday. No city in the world can compare to Sydney in the number of beaches scattered around it.\r\n\r\nSurrounded by beaches, mountains and parks, Sydney has something to attract tourists. But apparently not only its natural beauty is famous for Sydney, once he managed to turn from a convict settlement of the 17th century in the economic and cultural center of the 21st century, receiving more than 2.6 million tourists a year.','Adventure in Australia','','inherit','closed','closed','','111-revision-v1','','','2018-09-10 02:00:15','2018-09-09 23:00:15','',111,'http://mynomadtales.maunty.ru/111-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(136,1,'2018-09-10 02:00:30','2018-09-09 23:00:30','Africa-the second largest continent after Eurasia, is washed by the Mediterranean sea from the North, Red-from the North-East, the Atlantic ocean from the West and the Indian ocean from the East and South. Africa is also called part of the world, consisting of the continent of Africa and the surrounding Islands. The area of Africa without Islands is 29.2 million km2, with Islands — about 30.3 million km2[3], thus covering 6% of the total surface area of the Earth and 20.4% of the land surface. There are 55 States in Africa.\r\n\r\nAfrica has a population of about a billion people. Africa is considered the ancestral home of mankind: it is here that the oldest remains of early hominids and their probable ancestors were found, including the sahelanthropus, Avstralopitecus africanus , A. afarensis, Homo erectus, H. habilis and H. ergaster.\r\n\r\nThe African continent crosses the equator and several climatic zones; it is the only continent stretching from the Northern subtropical climatic zone to the southern subtropical. Due to lack of regular precipitation and irrigation as well as glaciers or mountain aquifer systems — the natural regulation of the climate anywhere except the coasts, is practically not observed.','Travel to Africa','','inherit','closed','closed','','107-revision-v1','','','2018-09-10 02:00:30','2018-09-09 23:00:30','',107,'http://mynomadtales.maunty.ru/107-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
